# Website Card Layout & Spacing Parity

Target customer portal contract. Applies when implementing or reviewing customer list cards as notification UI lands in `website/`.

Authority: `docs/invariants/website.md` W28 (card layout/spacing) + W29 (Utils-props-over-baseCssStyle).

## Non-negotiables

1. **No fixed card height.** Cards are content-driven.
2. **One responsive shell.** Image cards use `Col rotateAt={{maxW: SW.max_sm}}` when an image column exists.
3. **Shared spacing tokens.** Use `semanticDims.card.padding` / `semanticDims.card.compactPadding` for card padding and `semanticDims.page.sectionGap` for intra-content groups unless a card-specific token is added to `utils.ts`.
4. **Honest data only.** Show `metaUnavailable` or omit the row when the website GQL type has no real field for that data.
5. **`maxLi` needs a bounded width.** Give `Text` `w 100%` when centering via `ai_c` so line-clamp engages.
6. **Two-group pattern.** Separate primary content (title + chips) from trailing meta (time/summary) with distinct vertical spacing.

## Icon-row list cards (notifications)

Horizontal `Row` cards with a leading icon + text column use the two-group pattern inside the text column:

1. Text `Col` with two children when trailing meta exists — inner group for title + chips, trailing time/meta sibling below.
2. Trailing time/meta is not a chip sibling in the same inner group row.
3. Prefer `semanticDims` tokens over hardcoded rem literals when a token exists.
4. Loading skeleton mirrors the same grouping as the target card.

## Mandatory pre-ship checklist (any list card)

- [ ] Padding comes from `semanticDims.card` where applicable.
- [ ] Trailing meta uses separate spacing from chips/title groups.
- [ ] Loading skeleton matches the card grouping.

## baseCssStyle discipline (W29)

Use Utils props first. Reserve `baseCssStyle` for responsive overrides, media queries, and values with no Utils equivalent.

